22/03/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Leaders from Serbia and the Bosnian Serb entity, Republika Srpska (RS), held talks Tuesday (21 March) on co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal. 
Pressure is mounting on both governments ahead of an EU deadline for the handover of top war crimes fugitives. 
RS President Dragan Cavic, Serbian President Boris Tadic and Serbian Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica participated in the meeting. 
Serbia is under mounting pressure to track down Ratko Mladic, while RS and Montenegro are being urged to locate Radovan Karadzic. 
(Nezavisne novine - 22/03/06; AFP, PBS BiH, RTRS, RTS - 21/03/06)
